<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>How to Track Your Macros</title>
   
    <style>
          body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            text-align: left; /* Align the content within the body to the left */
        }

        header {
            background-color: #980303;
            color: #fff;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 1rem;
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 2rem;
        }

        main {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 2rem; /* Add margin to center the content within the page */
            padding: 2rem;
        }

        h2 {
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }

        p {
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
        }

        ul {
            margin-left: 1.5rem;
        }

        section:not(:first-child) {
            margin-top: 2rem;
        }

        footer {
            background-color: #333;
            color: #fff;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 1rem;
        }

        a {
            color: #007bff;
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        a:hover {
            text-decoration: underline;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>How to Track Your Macros</h1>
    </header>
    <main>
        <section>
            <h2>What are Macros?</h2>
            <p>Before we start tracking macros, let's understand what they are. Macros, short for macronutrients, are the three main nutrients that make up the caloric content of food:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Proteins</li>
                <li>Carbohydrates</li>
                <li>Fats</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section>
             <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/7HXkkanqPKA" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe>
            
            <h2>Step 1: Determine Your Goals</h2>
            <p>Decide whether you want to lose weight, gain muscle, or maintain your current weight. Your goals will determine the macro ratios you need.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Step 2: Calculate Your Macros</h2>
            <p>Use an online macro calculator or consult a nutritionist to calculate your daily macro needs based on your goals, age, weight, height, and activity level.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Step 3: Choose a Tracking Method</h2>
            <p>Decide how you want to track your macros. You can use mobile apps, online tools, or simply maintain a food journal.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Step 4: Start Tracking</h2>
            <p>Begin tracking your food intake daily. Enter the foods and their quantities to ensure you stay within your macro targets.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Step 5: Adjust as Needed</h2>
            <p>Monitor your progress and make adjustments to your macros if necessary. Remember that it's a dynamic process.</p>
        </section>
    </main>

    <!-- The macro calculator form and script go here -->
    <h1>Macronutrient Calculator</h1>
    <form>
        <label for="weight">Weight (in pounds):</label>
        <input type="number" id="weight" name="weight" step="0.1" required><br>

        <label for="height">Height (in feet):</label>
        <input type="number" id="height" name="height" step="0.01" required><br>

        <label for="age">Age:</label>
        <input type="number" id="age" name="age" required><br>

        <label for="activity-level">Activity Level:</label>
        <select id="activity-level" name="activity-level" required>
            <option value="sedentary">Sedentary (little to no exercise)</option>
            <option value="lightly-active">Lightly active (light exercise/sports 1-3 days/week)</option>
            <option value="moderately-active">Moderately active (moderate exercise/sports 3-5 days/week)</option>
            <option value="very-active">Very active (hard exercise/sports 6-7 days a week)</option>
            <option value="extra-active">Extra active (very hard exercise/sports and physical job or training)</option>
        </select><br>

        <input type="submit" value="Calculate Macros">
    </form>

    <div id="result"></div>

    <script>
        document.querySelector("form").addEventListener("submit", function(event) {
            event.preventDefault();

            const weightInPounds = parseFloat(document.getElementById("weight").value);
            const heightInFeet = parseFloat(document.getElementById("height").value);
            const age = parseInt(document.getElementById("age").value);
            const activityLevel = document.getElementById("activity-level").value;

            // Convert height to inches
            const heightInInches = heightInFeet * 12;

            // Calculate Basal Metabolic Rate (BMR) using the Mifflin-St Jeor Equation
            const bmr = 10 * weightInPounds + 6.25 * heightInInches - 5 * age + 5;

            // Adjust BMR based on activity level
            let tdee;
            switch (activityLevel) {
                case "sedentary":
                    tdee = bmr * 1.2;
                    break;
                case "lightly-active":
                    tdee = bmr * 1.375;
                    break;
                case "moderately-active":
                    tdee = bmr * 1.55;
                    break;
                case "very-active":
                    tdee = bmr * 1.725;
                    break;
                case "extra-active":
                    tdee = bmr * 1.9;
                    break;
                default:
                    tdee = bmr;
            }

            // Calculate macros (percentages may vary based on individual needs and goals)
            const proteinPercentage = 0.25;
            const carbohydratesPercentage = 0.55;
            const fatsPercentage = 0.20;

            const proteinGrams = Math.round((tdee * proteinPercentage) / 4);
            const carbohydratesGrams = Math.round((tdee * carbohydratesPercentage) / 4);
            const fatsGrams = Math.round((tdee * fatsPercentage) / 9);

            // Display the results
            const resultDiv = document.getElementById("result");
            resultDiv.innerHTML = `
                <h2>Your Macros:</h2>
                <p><strong>Protein:</strong> ${proteinGrams} grams</p>
                <p><strong>Carbohydrates:</strong> ${carbohydratesGrams} grams</p>
                <p><strong>Fats:</strong> ${fatsGrams} grams</p>
            `;
        });
    </script>

    <footer>
        &copy; 2023 Your Macros Tracker
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
